wiki_section_title: 4 x 5 km team ( 3 x 10 km : 1988–94 )

wiki_section_text: This involves each team taking one jump from the ski jumping large hill . For each one point difference between teams at the ski jump , there are 1.33 seconds between them at the start of the cross country skiing part of the competition . Point-time differentials for previous Olympics are as follows : 1988–1994 – 1 pt = 5 seconds , 1998 – 1 pt = 3 seconds , 2002 – 1 pt = 1.5 seconds , 2006 – 1 pt = 1 second .
